"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-lebron-james-team-usa-flag-bearer-2024-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Opening Ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics is only days away, and as always, the host nation is planning a visual and auditory extravaganza to blow viewers away.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 166, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 20}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 24, \"to\": 33}, {\"ngram\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 34, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"the host nation\", \"from\": 82, \"to\": 97}, {\"ngram\": \"a visual and auditory extravaganza\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 144}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is giving the world anOpening Ceremonythe likes of which it has never seen before, with athletes being sent on a river parade down the Seine.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8068647642149862, \"rank\": 0.2380977612329797, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999983424813857, \"rank\": 9.087340859931176e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"Ceremonythe likes\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"a river parade\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the first time that an Olympics Opening Ceremony will not be held in a stadium, and fans will not want to miss it.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 338}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 402}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 412}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As of 2020, every participating nation is allowed two flag bearers (one male and one female) for the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.803977261592564, \"rank\": 0.23910905015861805, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every participating nation\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"two flag bearers\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"one male\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"one female\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being chosen to carry the flag is one of the greatest honors an athlete can receive, not only because these athletes get the chance to represent their country on such a tremendous stage but because the flag bearer is determined by a vote of their peers in a poll conducted by the Team USA Athletes' Commission.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999954261127197, \"rank\": 4.555536138264249e-06, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest honors\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 619}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"such a tremendous stage\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag bearer\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 772}, {\"ngram\": \"a vote\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"their peers\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"a poll\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 821}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are still waiting to find out which female athlete will represent the United States delegation, but the male flag bearer has been announced, and it's a name people might have heard of before.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999941024524298, \"rank\": 5.015974149793382e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"which female athlete\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"the male flag bearer\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1030}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's right, LeBron James will be adding to his list of accolades by carrying the U.S. flag in the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 1.329861292706979e-11, \"text\": \"U.S. flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his list\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"accolades\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1182}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James is one of the greatest and most recognizable athletes in the world.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the greatest and most recognizable athletes\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is little he has not done on the basketball court, both in the NBA, where he's won four MVPs and four championships and at the Olympics, where he's won a bronze medal (2004) and two golds (2008 and 2012).\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9098102306094827e-12, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the basketball court\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"four MVPs\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"four championships\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze medal\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be his fourth Olympics, making him one of the senior members of the team, and it's a clear statement that the United States is there to win.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999941024524298, \"rank\": 5.015974149793382e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his fourth Olympics\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"the senior members\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"a clear statement\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For James, it's the latest milestone in a truly singular career.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the latest milestone\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"a truly singular career\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's the first men's basketball player to represent the U.S. as a flag bearer, and he joins Dawn Staley and Sue Bird as the only other basketball players from this country to receive the honor.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dawn Staley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Staley\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sue Bird\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first men's basketball player\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"a flag bearer\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"the only other basketball players\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"this country\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"the honor\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as the quality of basketball around the world has greatly improved in the past couple of decades, the U.S. men's team is still a heavy favorite to once again win gold.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9010036412678639, \"rank\": 0.10969180822263297, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"the past couple\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1983}, {\"ngram\": \"a heavy favorite\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, it's far from a sure thing, as Saturday's shockingly close tune-up game with South Sudan proved.James saved the U.S.from one of the most astonishing upsets in international basketball history by scoring 25 points and sinking a layup with eight seconds left to complete a 16-point comeback and secure a 101-100 U.S. win.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sure thing\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday's shockingly close tune-up game\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"South Sudan\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2150}, {\"ngram\": \"James\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"the most astonishing upsets\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"international basketball history\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2253}, {\"ngram\": \"25 points\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"a layup\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"eight seconds\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2313}, {\"ngram\": \"a 16-point comeback\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"a 101-100 U.S. win\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James has been in the headlines recently due to theLakers drafting his son Bronny, and for the ongoing conversation about whether retirement could be in the cards for him in the next couple of years.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999993102408203, \"rank\": 6.154499184685807e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the headlines\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 241